    <section>
      <h2><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info icon-blue"></i> 1. What This App Does</h2>
      <p>SQL Query Tester helps you:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Write and run <strong>SQL queries directly</strong></li>
        <li>Use <strong>AI to generate SQL</strong> from natural language</li>
        <li>View query results in clean, formatted tables</li>
        <li>Manage demo database (reset / clear tables)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2><i class="fa-solid fa-terminal icon-green"></i> 2. Using Direct SQL</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Open the <strong>Direct SQL</strong> tab.</li>
        <li>Type or paste an SQL query.</li>
        <li>Click <strong>Execute Query</strong> to run it.</li>
        <li>Results will appear below.</li>
      </ol>
      <div class="note">
        üí° Example: <code>SELECT * FROM Books;</code>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2><i class="fa-solid fa-robot icon-blue"></i> 3. Using AI (Natural Language)</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Go to the <strong>Natural Language</strong> tab.</li>
        <li>Type your question in plain English.</li>
        <li>Click <strong>Generate SQL</strong>.</li>
        <li>Review and edit if needed.</li>
        <li>Click <strong>Execute Generated SQL</strong> to run.</li>
      </ol>
      <div class="note">
        ‚ú® Example: Type <em>"Show all books with their authors"</em><br />
        AI generates:<br />
        <code>
          SELECT b.Title, a.FirstName, a.LastName<br />
          FROM Books b JOIN Authors a ON b.AuthorID = a.AuthorID;
        </code>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2><i class="fa-solid fa-triangle-exclamation icon-yellow"></i> 4. Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Case Sensitivity:</strong>  
          Keywords (<code>SELECT</code>, <code>FROM</code>) are safe, but table/column names might be case sensitive.  
          Example: <code>Books</code> ‚â† <code>books</code>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Missing Semicolons:</strong> Always end queries with <code>;</code></li>
        <li><strong>Invalid Joins:</strong> Ensure join columns exist.</li>
        <li><strong>Empty Queries:</strong> Executing nothing will fail.</li>
        <li><strong>AI SQL Edits:</strong> Double-check generated SQL for accuracy.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

